dc_description_s: This data represents public boat access sites for Wisconsin in 2021. [This dataset is maintained by Wisconsin Department of Natural Resources. It is a compilation of public sites where boats can be legally launched into public waters in Wisconsin. It includes locations and data for both ramp and carry-in (canoe/kayak) launch sites throughout the state. These public launch sites are owned and maintained by State government (i.e. DNR, DOT, etc.) and local municipalities. No privately-owned sites are included in this database. This dataset is continually being updated and added to; this item displays the most current edits, however it may contain errors or omissions.]
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most current data available, please visit: https://data-wi-dnr.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/public-boat-access-sites?geometry=-105.161%2C41.937%2C-74.333%2C47.400
